<figureCitation id="130BF280404DFFCBE344050D3634F8B8" box="[257,286,1798,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,267,1631]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 19. Pleurotrocha fontanetoi sp. nov., SEM photographs of trophi. A. Complete set, ventral; B. incus, ventral; C. incus, lateral right; D. right uncus, inner view; E. distal part of ribbon of short and long sclerite bodies; F. left manubrium, outer view; G. right manubrium, outer view; H. incus, oblique ventro-caudal; I, J. complete set, oblique ventro-frontal. R: ribbon of sclerite bodies. Scale bars: A − D, F − J: 10 µm; E: 1 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240575/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">19</figureCitation>
