<subSubSection id="C32ABD8E404DFFCBE2D205463609F874" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE05404DFFCBE2D205463609F874" blockId="22.[151,1436,1869,2002]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B9443217404DFFCBE2D20546363BF8C0" bold="true" box="[151,273,1869,1894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head short, narrower than trunk; foot long, 
<number id="3DF8FC22404DFFCBE14B05453410F8C0" box="[782,826,1870,1894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2−3</number>
pseudosegments; toes conical, with offset distal half; corona slightly oblique; rami with long obtuse alulae; fulcrum with large basal plate; manubria with large head and incurved cauda; a ribbon composed of two bands of short and long sclerite bodies laterally from dorsally recurved part of rami.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF4FBE8D404CFFCAE2D207A0348BFA58" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240573/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" targetBox="[151,1436,193,1428]" targetPageId="23">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE05404CFFCAE2D207A0348BFA58" blockId="23.[151,1436,1451,1534]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B9443217404CFFCAE2D207A03609FA67" bold="true" box="[151,291,1451,1473]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">FIGURE 17.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C309586404CFFCAE36807A036F3FA67" box="[301,473,1451,1473]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lindiidae" genus="Lindia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aequorea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9443217404CFFCAE36807A036F3FA67" box="[301,473,1451,1473]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Lindia aequorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2778F6C404CFFCAE3A607A0351DFA67" box="[483,567,1451,1473]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9443217404CFFCAE3A607A0351DFA67" bold="true" box="[483,567,1451,1473]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, SEM photographs of trophi. A. Complete set, ventral; B. same as A, frontal; C. complete set, lateral; D. epipharynx; E. left uncus, without preuncinal tooth and subuncus; F. right uncus, with preuncinal tooth and subuncus; G. left preuncinal tooth; H. right subuncus. Scale bars: 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C32ABD8E404CFFCAE282042036D3F8E6" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE05404CFFCAE28204203328F9C1" blockId="23.[151,1437,1579,2036]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B9443217404CFFCAE2820420364DF9E2" bold="true" box="[199,359,1579,1604]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<typeStatus id="548B50A7404CFFCAE28204203628F9E2" box="[199,258,1579,1604]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
Punta della Madonna di Ponente, Elba Island, Tyrrhenian Sea, 
<collectingCountry id="F327AE95404CFFCAE6790420335BF9E2" box="[1084,1137,1579,1604]" name="Italy" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Italy</collectingCountry>
. In psammon collected on 
<date id="FF8EC8C5404CFFCAE2D204443632F9CE" box="[151,280,1615,1640]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" value="2006-09-28">
<number id="3DF8FC22404CFFCAE2D2044437F3F9CE" box="[151,217,1615,1640]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" value="28.09">28.09</number>
.2006
</date>
