<subSubSection id="C32ABD8E4043FFC5E282052C3446F853" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE054043FFC5E282052C3446F853" blockId="24.[151,1436,1615,2037]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis id="B94432174043FFC5E282052C3665F8E6" bold="true" box="[199,335,1831,1856]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Comments.</emphasis>
The species is allocated to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3095864043FFC5E0AA052C3368F8E6" authority="Ehrenberg, 1830" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1830" box="[751,1090,1831,1856]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Notommatidae" genus="Pleurotrocha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Rotifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94432174043FFC5E0AA052C34A8F8E6" box="[751,898,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Pleurotrocha</emphasis>
Ehrenberg, 
<number id="3DF8FC224043FFC5E64F05233368F8E6" box="[1034,1090,1832,1856]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="1830.0">1830</number>
</taxonomicName>
on basis of the stout body with well-separated head and trunk, the long cylindrical foot with two short toes, the sligthtly oblique corona with lateral tufts of cilia, auricles absent, a single cerebral eyespot, and fairly large pedal glands with reservoir; the trophi are virgate, with long fulcrum and dorsally recurved rami (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA193F44043FFC5E15C059F3488F80A" author="Koste" box="[793,930,1940,1964]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" refString="Koste, W. (1978) Rotatoria. Die Radertiere Mitteleuropas. Ein Bestimmungswerk, begrundet von Max Voigt. Ueberordnung Monogononta. 2 nd Edition. Gebr. Borntraeger, Berlin, Stuttgart, I. Textband, 673 pp., II. Tafelband, 234 Taf." type="book" year="1978">
Koste 
<number id="3DF8FC224043FFC5E122059F3488F80A" box="[871,930,1940,1964]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA193F44043FFC5E1F5059F33B4F80B" author="Nogrady" box="[944,1182,1940,1965]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" refString="Nogrady, T., Pourriot, R. &amp; Segers, H. (1995) The Notommatidae and the Scaridiidae. In: Nogrady, T. (Ed.), Rotifera 3. Vol. 8. Guides to the Identification of the Microinvertebrates of the Continental Waters of the World. SPB Academic Publishing bv., The Hague, 248 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Nogrady 
<emphasis id="B94432174043FFC5E658059E3372F80B" box="[1053,1112,1940,1965]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DF8FC224043FFC5E627059F33B4F80B" box="[1122,1182,1940,1965]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In fixed material, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3095864043FFC5E7C2059E3623F876" class="Eurotatoria" family="Notommatidae" genus="Pleurotrocha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="fontanetoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94432174043FFC5E7C2059E3623F876" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">P. fontanetoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2778F6C4043FFC5E34A05BC3643F876" box="[271,361,1975,2000]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B94432174043FFC5E34A05BC3643F876" bold="true" box="[271,361,1975,2000]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be mistaken for 
<taxonomicName id="4C3095864043FFC5E01705BC34E3F876" authority="Beauchamp, 1907" authorityName="Beauchamp" authorityYear="1907" box="[594,969,1975,2000]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Proalidae" genus="Proales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B94432174043FFC5E01705BC35D2F876" box="[594,760,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Proales similis</emphasis>
Beauchamp, 
<number id="3DF8FC224043FFC5E1D405B334E3F876" box="[913,969,1976,2000]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="1907.0">1907</number>
</taxonomicName>
but is unambiguously differentiated from the latter and all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C3095864043FFC5E3D105D73510F853" box="[404,570,2012,2037]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Notommatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Rotifera" rank="family">Notommatidae</taxonomicName>
by its characteristic trophi.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ABD8E4042FFC4E282029C3219FF72" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE054042FFC4E282029C3219FF72" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis id="B94432174042FFC4E282029C36D5FF16" bold="true" box="[199,511,151,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
The species was found in psammon from the Côte d’Azur and Elba Island, Tyrrhenian Sea, 
<quantity id="4CC843E04042FFC4E30A02B736A2FF72" box="[335,392,188,213]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" unit="m" value="50.0">50 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity id="4CC843E04042FFC4E3FB02B736DDFF73" box="[446,503,188,213]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
off shore, depth 
<quantity id="4CC843E04042FFC4E0F002B73436FF72" box="[693,796,188,212]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" unit="m" value="30.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="20.0">20−40 m</quantity>
, June, September, water temperature 
<number id="3DF8FC224042FFC4E6FA02B7322DFF72" box="[1215,1287,188,212]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" value="20.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="17.0">17−23</number>
°C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
